{"type":"compaction","id":"a880ce2c","parentId":"99e7c9e5","timestamp":"2026-04-04T14:34:52.786Z","summary":"## Goal\nWrite a comprehensive Chinese technical article about \"Harness Engineering\" for internal team sharing (algorithm team: senior+mid-level engineers). The article should cover the theoretical framework, different vendors' engineering practices with detailed comparisons, and the \"heavy engineering vs heavy model\" debate. A future section on extending Harness Engineering to business scenarios is planned but not yet written.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Language: Chinese, with technical terms kept in English\n- Style: 深入浅出 (accessible yet rigorous/academic)\n- \"Harness Engineering\" is the author's proposed interpretive abstraction, NOT an industry standard term — must not present it as consensus or official definition\n- Do NOT attribute Harness as something Anthropic \"proposed\" — they described Agent/Workflow problems that can be interpreted through the Harness lens\n- Structure around three core challenges (\"问题三角\"): Context Rot, Context Reset, Self-Evaluation Bias — all vendor sections and cross-comparisons must map back to these three\n- Claude Code belongs under the Anthropic chapter (not a separate open-source section); OpenClaw gets its own chapter\n- Exclude Microsoft (AutoGen) from detailed analysis\n- Harness Engineering is inference-driven, not process-driven — the model drives, Harness ensures the Agent Loop doesn't deviate from goals\n- Harness Engineering ≠ Workflow Orchestrator — must distinguish (deterministic orchestration vs non-deterministic LLM control)\n- Trends described as \"trends\" not \"consensus\"; multi-agent framed with qualifiers (\"in complex/long-running scenarios\")\n- No unverified technical claims (e.g., Opus 4.6 specifics)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Read and analyzed all source articles from `/Users/lvzheng/Downloads/harness-articles-collection.md` (Anthropic, Cursor, OpenAI, Google — excluding Microsoft)\n- [x] Read and analyzed OpenClaw source code at `/Users/lvzheng/Cursor/openclaw` (Context Engine interface, compaction, subagent system, skills, plugins, system prompt assembly)\n- [x] Read and analyzed Claude Code leaked source at `/Users/lvzheng/Cursor/claude-code` (QueryEngine, compact/microCompact/autoCompact/SessionMemory, Coordinator Mode, AgentTool, agentMemory, BashTool permissions)\n- [x] Wrote initial draft (~12,000 chars)\n- [x] Renamed \"Harness\" → \"Harness Engineering\" throughout\n- [x] Rewrote intro: Harness as \"收敛性抽象\" not \"2024 high-frequency term\"; added disclaimer that it's the author's abstraction\n- [x] Added \"Harness: from software engineering old concept to AI new life\" section (Test Harness → Evaluation Harness → AI Agent Harness, with lm-evaluation-harness reference)\n- [x] Restructured: Claude Code merged into Anthropic chapter; OpenClaw as standalone chapter\n- [x] Restructured all vendor sections to map practices against \"问题三角\" with response tables\n- [x] Restructured Section 7 cross-comparison to organize by three challenges (7.1 Context Rot, 7.2 Context Reset, 7.3 Self-Evaluation Bias)\n- [x] Removed redundant \"模型 vs 工程\" subsection (kept debate in Section 8)\n- [x] Added \"Harness Engineering ≠ Workflow Orchestrator\" distinction paragraph\n- [x] Added \"推理驱动 not 流程驱动\" paragraph with driver/safety-belt analogy\n- [x] Fixed \"单次对话\" ambiguity → \"任务复杂度高 + 会话跨度长\" with clarification that Q&A can also be multi-turn\n- [x] Added inline explanation for Self-Summarization at first mention\n- [x] Fixed Opus 4.6 description: reverted from unverified \"检索准确率提升\" to conservative \"消除了上下文焦虑\" faithful to source, with note that it's not about window size\n- [x] Softened Anthropic attribution in 3 places\n- [x] Downgraded multi-agent language from \"主流选择\" to \"结构性趋势\" with qualifiers\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] User reviewing latest version; may have more feedback\n- [ ] Future: \"业务延伸\" section — user wants to discuss before writing\n\n### Blocked\n- (none)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Article file location**: `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-circle/Harness技术实践对比.md` (~22KB current)\n- **\"问题三角\" as structural backbone**: All vendor sections and cross-comparisons organized around Context Rot / Context Reset / Self-Evaluation Bias\n- **Conservative attribution**: No unverified model technical claims; Opus 4.6 described per source only\n- **Harness as control plane**: Explicitly distinguished from Workflow Orchestrator; framed as serving model inference, not replacing it\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Wait for user's next round of feedback on the current version\n2. Apply any further revisions user requests\n3. When user is ready, discuss and write the \"业务延伸\" section (Harness Engineering extending from engineering methodology to business scenarios)\n\n## Critical Context\n- Article file: `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-circle/Harness技术实践对比.md`\n- Source articles: `/Users/lvzheng/Downloads/harness-articles-collection.md`\n- OpenClaw source: `/Users/lvzheng/Cursor/openclaw` — key files: `src/context-engine/types.ts` (pluggable ContextEngine interface), `src/agents/compaction.ts` (simple compaction), `src/agents/subagent-spawn.ts`, `src/agents/skills.ts`, `src/agents/system-prompt.ts` (PromptMode: full/minimal/none)\n- Claude Code source: `/Users/lvzheng/Cursor/claude-code` — key files: `services/compact/compact.ts`, `services/compact/autoCompact.ts`, `services/compact/microCompact.ts`, `services/SessionMemory/sessionMemory.ts`, `coordinator/coordinatorMode.ts`, `tools/AgentTool/agentMemory.ts` (user/project/local scopes), `tools/BashTool/` (segmented permission checks)\n- Identity files: `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-circle/IDENTITY.md`, `SOUL.md`\n- Memory: `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-circle/memory/2026-04-04.md`\n- User has not provided their name yet\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user shared Claude 4.6's detailed peer review of an article about \"Harness Engineering\" practices across AI coding assistants (Anthropic, Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, Google ADK, OpenClaw). The review identified accuracy issues, content gaps, and formatting suggestions.\n\n## Early Progress\nThe assistant began applying fixes to `Harness技术实践对比.md` based on the review:\n1. Added footnote marker to GAN analogy\n2. Expanded Self-Evaluation Bias section with academic terms (Sycophancy, RLHF causes)\n3. Added \"V1 版本\" time qualifier to HuggingFace Leaderboard reference\n4. Removed unanalyzed Microsoft AutoGen from references\n5. **Major rewrite**: Replaced Opus 4.6 section with detailed Context Reset vs Compaction engineering insight (Sonnet 4.5 era needed resets; Opus 4.6 largely removed context anxiety)\n6. Strengthened Codex critique (trade-off: isolation certainty vs accumulation continuity)\n7. Added Context Reset detail to Opus 4.6 mention in section 8\n8. Added Generator self-evaluation nuance to Claude Code section\n9. Merged three separate comparison tables (7.1, 7.2, 7.3) into one unified three-dimensional comparison table\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- Working file: `/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-circle/Harness技术实践对比.md`\n- 11 replacements were applied in the tool call\n- Still pending from the review: fixing the \"Harness Engineering\" terminology framing (clarify it's author's framework vs industry consensus), clarifying the \"problem triangle\" attribution (author's synthesis vs Anthropic's original), adding more opinion in section 8's conclusion, trimming redundant analogies in introduction, adding pseudocode/flowcharts, unifying reference formats, adding GAN footnote content, and adding article metadata line","firstKeptEntryId":"16eb52dd","tokensBefore":137855,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":false}
{"type":"message","id":"20cf262f","parentId":"a880ce2c","timestamp":"2026-04-04T14:35:08.659Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bae60116f069470ea7f9f0cd","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/lvzheng/.openclaw/workspace-assistant-circle/fix_coordinator.py","content":"# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\nwith open('Harness技术实践对比.md', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# 1. Enhance Coordinator section - add three-layer architecture\nold1 = '#### 回应自我评估偏差：Coordinator Mode\\n\\nClaude Code 实现了一个 Coordinator 模式，系统提示中明确：'\nnew1 = '''#### 回应自我评估偏差：Coordinator Mode\n\nClaude Code 实现了一个 Coordinator 模式。要理解这个模式，需要先理解它的三层架构：\n\n**代码层（硬约束）**：Coordinator 拥有工具定义——如 `Task` 工具（spawn 子 Agent）、`SendMessage`（向已有 Agent 发消息）、`TaskStop`（终止 Agent）。这些是代码层面的能力，模型必须通过调用工具才能实际创建和管理 Worker。没有工具，光靠提示词无法派任务。\n\n**提示词层（软约束）**：系统提示定义了 Coordinator 的角色和工作流程——\"你是 Coordinator，你应该先 Research，再 Synthesis，再 Implementation，再 Verification\"等。系统提示不是 if-else 语句，它是对模型行为的引导。模型读到它，倾向于按照它行事，但在特定情况下也可以偏离。\n\n**模型推理层（动态）**：具体决策由模型推理完成——查哪些文件、需要几个 Worker、这个任务 spawn 还是自己做。模型的\"决定\"通过 tool call 具体化：当模型输出一个 `Task` 调用，决策就被执行。Harness 负责把 tool call 变成实际运行的子 Agent 进程，模型不需要知道背后的实现细节。\n\nClaude Code 的系统提示中明确写道：'''\n\nassert old1 in content, 'Pattern 1 not found!'\ncontent = content.replace(old1, new1)\n\n# 2. Add the philosophy insight\nold2 = '这是一个**硬编码的经验总结**——不是让模型\"自己学会如何协调\"，而是直接告诉它\"这样最好\"。它凝结了大规模实践中积累的教训。'\nnew2 = '''这是一个**硬编码的经验总结**——不是让模型\"自己学会如何协调\"，而是直接告诉它\"这样最好\"。它凝结了大规模实践中积累的教训。提示词写得如此详细，正是因为它是唯一的\"约束手段\"——越详细、越具体，模型偏离的概率就越低。\n\n这其实就是 Anthropic 整个设计哲学的缩影：**模型只管推理和决策，Harness 只管执行和编排，两者通过工具定义这个接口连接。** 这也是为什么模型越强，Coordinator 就越可靠——不是因为代码变了，而是因为遵循提示词的能力和任务规划的能力都在提升。'''\n\nassert old2 in content, 'Pattern 2 not found!'\ncontent = content.replace(old2, new2)\n\nwith open('Harness技术实践对比.md', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    f.write(content)\nprint('Done - 2 replacements')\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5-turbo","usage":{"input":30428,"output":650,"cacheRead":17582,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48660,"cost":{"input":0.0365136,"output":0.0026,"cacheRead":0.00421968,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.04333328}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775313292894,"responseId":"20260404223456220edb6d26414fbd"}}
